  "prompt": "I told him I liked him and he didn't give me an actual answer! Help?",
  "response": "It can be really frustrating and confusing when someone doesn\u2019t give you a clear response after you\u2019ve opened up about your feelings. Here\u2019s how you can approach the situation:\n\n### 1. **Give Him Some Time**\n   - He might need time to process what you\u2019ve said and figure out how he feels. People often react differently when caught off guard, and he may not have been ready to respond immediately.\n\n### 2. **Clarify Your Expectations**\n   - If you\u2019re feeling uncertain, it\u2019s okay to gently bring it up again. You could say something like, *\u201cI just wanted to check in because I shared how I felt, and I wasn\u2019t sure if you had any thoughts about it. I understand if you need more time, but I\u2019d love to hear your perspective when you\u2019re ready.\u201d*\n\n### 3. **Pay Attention to His Actions**\n   - Sometimes people struggle to express their feelings verbally, but their actions can speak volumes. If he\u2019s still spending time with you, being attentive, or showing interest, it could be a sign that he\u2019s into you but unsure how to respond.\n\n### 4. **Consider the Possibility of Mixed Feelings**\n   - He might not be sure how he feels yet, or he might be hesitant for reasons unrelated to you (e.g., past experiences, fear of commitment, etc.). If he\u2019s honest about his uncertainty, it\u2019s a sign that he\u2019s taking your feelings seriously.\n\n### 5. **Prepare Yourself for Any Outcome**\n   - While it\u2019s important to be hopeful, also be ready for the possibility that he may not feel the same way. If that\u2019s the case, remind yourself that his response doesn\u2019t define your worth, and it\u2019s better to know now than to keep wondering.\n\n### 6. **Take Care of Yourself**\n   - Waiting for a reply can be emotionally draining. Focus on things that make you happy and build your confidence, whether it\u2019s spending time with friends, pursuing hobbies, or practicing self-care.\n\nRemember, you were brave for being honest about your feelings, and that\u2019s something to be proud of. Whatever happens next, you\u2019ll handle it with grace and strength!",
